      • constructFromText

        public static CharMatrix constructFromText(int row,
                                           int col,
                                           java.lang.String text)
        Returns a new object with the given size (row X col), initialized with the given text row-wise. The size of the bare string should be (row * col) characters. If it's bigger, then it will be truncated from the right, and if it's smaller, then it returns null.
        Parameters:
        row - the given row size
        col - the given column size
        text - the given text (string of characters)
        Returns:
        a new object

      • permuteColsM

        public CharMatrix permuteColsM(int[] colsPerm)
        Mutable permutes the columns of this object based on the given array. For example, if (2,0,1) is passed, then, in fact, it means (0,1,2) -> (2,0,1) and this means the col #0 of this matrix goes to two, col #1 goes to the zero, and col #2 goes to one. Note that the columns' numbers are zero-based.
        Parameters:
        colsPerm - the list of permutations.
        Returns:
        this object
